= SDL_WaitEventTimeout =
Use this function to wait until the specified timeout (in milliseconds) for the next available event.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_WaitEventTimeout(SDL_Event* event,
                         int        timeout)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''event'''
|if not NULL, the next event is removed from the queue and stored in that area ,,'''event''',,
|-
|'''timeout'''
|^the number of milliseconds to wait for the next available event^
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 1 on success, or 0 if there was an error while waiting for events; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

